        {
          "commText": "On the other hand, MI are in a much more desperate situation sitting 9th on the table. This is a must-win game for them to stay relevant in the tournament. MI’s biggest hope is the opening duo of Rohit Sharma and Ryan Rickelton as their middle order (Suryakumar Yadav and Hardik Pandya) have struggled for consistency. There were many rumors that Suryakumar Yadav might miss this match because he recently went home for the birth of his daughter. However, latest reports confirm he is flying into Raipur just hours before the game and will be available to play. His return is a huge boost for MI, especially since captain Hardik Pandya is still being checked for a back injury. History is on MI's side with a 19-16 lead in head-to-head matches, but RCB have won most of their recent meetings. All eyes will be on Virat Kohli, who needs just 28 more runs to reach 1,000 career runs against Mumbai. Stay tuned for toss and team updates in a bit.",
          "timestamp": 1778417587202,
          "ballNbr": 0,
          "event": "NONE",
          "batTeamName": "",
          "commentaryFormats": {},
          "batsmanStriker": {
